reviews.review_text: nice AUD Nice Job on the cleaning, being 33 yrs old and all, crowd is fun on this tape, worth the collection if AUDs are your thang...

great 76 missing the encore which can be found in another source, other source is all jumbled though, both sound pretty similar which is great for this aud!

lot of great tunes in the first set here including a great tenn jed

the might as well to start the second set is nice and has an interesting jam in the outro to samson, really cool, candyman is great, playing is different interesting and good and the rest of the show from then on is great, love wharf

A must have I love this show.  The jamming is as good as it gets and the flow of the 2nd set is just exactly perfect.  There's even a little transition jam out of Might As Well to open the 2nd set.   The Wharf Rat is fabulous, and the Playin' reprise is to die for.  

I've heard better Aud recordings, but this one is pretty good.

Mighty Swell! its great... reminds me when I would listen through the hiss and crowd noise to hear a great performance... or even not so great. the band is in great form and it has many sparkling moments. the problem is I am so used to hearing fine soundboards and this one thus falls under less than perfect. as such likely not one I will return to again and again. The show and the band's performance deserve better... sometimes it just goes to show, you might as well, might as well!
